N2  - The aim of this literature review is to explore stigma as experienced by individuals with mental health problems, focusing primarily on schizophrenia. The concept of stigma has been examined. Service users' reports of their experiences of stigma have been outlined. The role of the media, public perceptions and the role of the nurses and mental health services have been discussed. Proposals have been suggested to address stigma. (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2021 APA, all rights reserved)
